ve been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hugh MacDuff of Fife was born in 1135, in Fife, Scotland, his father, Hugh MacDuff, was 30 and his mother, Mrs. Hugh MacDuff, was 26. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Hugh MacDuff. He died about 1195, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1135–about 1195":"1135–umbes 1195","1135–1195":"1135–1195","1138–Female":"1138–Surnud","1165–1214":"1165–1214","1105–Male":"1105–Surnud","1109–Female":"1109–Surnud","about 1195":"umbes 1195","1105":"1105","1138":"1138","1214":"1214","1135":"1135","1165":"1165","1195":"1195","1109":"1109","Coaltown of Wemyss, Fife, Scotland":"Wemyss, Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland"},"fi":{"1135–about 1195":"1135–noin 1195","1135–1195":"1135–1195","1138–Female":"1138–Kuollut","1165–1214":"1165–1214","1105–Male":"1105–Kuollut","1109–Female":"1109–Kuollut","about 1195":"noin 1195","1105":"1105","1138":"1138","1214":"1214","1135":"1135","1165":"1165","1195":"1195","1109":"1109","Coaltown of Wemyss, Fife, Scotland":"Wemyss, Fife, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland"},"fr":{"1135–about 1195":"1135–environ 1195","1135–1195":"1135–1195","1138–Female":"1138–Décédée","1165–1214":"1165–1214","1105–Male":"1105–Décédé","1109–Female":"1109–Décédée","about 1195":"environ 1195","1105":"1105","1138":"1138","1214":"1214","1135":"1135","1165":"1165","1195":"1195","1109":"1109","Coaltown of Wemyss, Fife, Scotland":"Wemyss, Fife, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Écosse","lifeSumma